        "id": 1015244
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-17T07:58:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t understand why we have to implement this now.\nIf we can\u0027t handle a message `A` synchronously (after all the retry attempts), eventually we will give up.\nWe shouldn\u0027t ack message `A`, since we haven\u0027t processed it correctly.\n\nHowever, the next `polling` might still give the next message `B` in the partition.\nIf we do manage to process `B` correctly, we would be implicitly acking `A`, which would be wrong.\n\nThis is exactly issue [529865773](https://issues.gerritcodereview.com/issues/529865773), and I thought we should have handled what to do as part of _that_ effort.\n\nHaving this change decide on `requeuing` (rather than DLQ, dropping, or any other strategies) seems arbitrary and too much for this change.",
      "parentUuid": "85ac17ac_b4f37e81",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "428c6319870ee9443741d9430aa4cf54b5297def",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "69c4980a_d6ccbbbe",
        "filename": "src/main/java/com/gerritforge/gerrit/plugins/multisite/consumer/AbstractSubcriber.java",
        "patchSetId": 64
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 1015244
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-17T15:19:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Discussed f2f.\nThe reason we have to implement this now is that we **cannot** wait for a potentially long time for an event to be handled, because that could potentially hold up the consumption of the entire partition for a long time.\n\nThe current proposed solution is to acknowledge the current event, but first requeue it so that it can be attempted again later, without holding up the queue.\n\nWe discussed the concern that this reordering might affect the final state, but it is not the case since INDEX operations are idempotent.",
      "parentUuid": "7cef35e3_54f291b0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "428c6319870ee9443741d9430aa4cf54b5297def",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
