        "id": 1000000
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-17T07:20:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I think we might be acking too eagerly here.\n\u003e \n\u003e `broker.send()` is asynchronous\n\nThe lines of code do not call `broker.send()` but `requeueAction.requeue(event)` which must be synchronous.\n\nThe comment should be for the block where the `requeueAction` is implemented.\n\n\u003e but `RequeueEventAction` returns `void`, so we acknowledge the original but we don\u0027t know whether the new copy was published successfully and ff the publish fails, the event is lost.\n\nGood point, so we need to ensure that `requeueAction` returns a `boolean` and ack the message *only if* the requeue was successful.",
