      "lineNbr": 85,
      "author": {
        "id": 1015244
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-17T15:19:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "An update on all index-events behaviour when deleted.\n\n* *GROUP* - Once removed, a group cannot be re-created; it will have a new group id.\n* *ACCOUNT* - Once removed, an account cannot be re-created; it will have a new account id.\n* *CHANGE* - Once removed, a change cannot be re-created; it will be a new change.\n* *PROJECT* - Once removed, there is no project-index message that is sent: the reindex gets handled by the project_list_update handler, which removes from the projectCache and then removes the project from the index.\n\nSo you were right @luca.milanesio@gmail.com\nGiven the above, I think we are fine, because it is not possible to have the inversion of delete and index messages.",
      "parentUuid": "ec00eb68_708a4ef4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 85,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 85,
        "endChar": 72
      },
      "revId": "428c6319870ee9443741d9430aa4cf54b5297def",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
